IMPORTANT INFORMATION FOR STUDENTS AND PARENTS

Due to the City of Archie having to shut the water off today, we will be under a boil order until further notice. Please send your students to school with a full bottle of water each day, as they will not be able to fill them here at the school.

If your student runs out of water during the day, the district will have bottled water available. We will update you when the boil order is lifted. Thank you for your flexibility and understanding.

post_text:
Hello families,

It has been a joy to see kids returning to the activities they love on the field and on the court. It is very important to me that we begin the year in a positive way, focused on the true spirit of student athletics and activities. While games are competitive, they are also an educational experience for players and students. Parents, fans, and people in the community all set an example for students whether they are aware of it or not. That is why it is imperative that all spectators show respect and sportsmanship and refrain from negative cheers, chants, or behavior. Let’s enjoy every game this season by cheering on our athletes and supporting our coaches and officials who make these events possible. Thank you for following our 24 hour policy before speaking with coaches after games, and for keeping those conversations professional. With your support, we can all look forward to a fantastic year.

Michelle Gaddie
Archie High School Principal

post_text:
Archie R-V had an amazing first day of school! It was wonderful having students back in the building. A BIG shout out goes to our bus drivers, parents, student drivers, daycare providers and staff for their patience and flexibility as we navigated our new arrival/dismissal procedures.
Many times we worry about students' ability to do new things.
Today was a perfect example of how students EXCEED our expectations. Students showed up today excited, enthusiastic and ready to learn! They were exemplary in their ability to follow proper masking, social distancing, and hand sanitizing protocol.
We truly have great students and staff at Archie R-V!! #ArchieStrong

JH students entering 7th and 8th grade, who are interested in JH Cheerleading, please e-mail Coach Lesli Lame at llame@archie.k12.mo.us

JH Football Parents:

Parents,

I hope everyone is enjoying the summer. I wanted to take a moment to reach out to everyone and touch base about the upcoming jr high football season.

I know from a meeting with the kids at the end of last season that there is a good number of students who are wanting to play football next year. I’ve set up a class on the Remind application called Archie Jr High Football 2020. This link will allow you to join that group https://www.remind.com/join/archiejr
You can also text @archiejr to 81010 to join.

If your child does plan on playing, or is considering playing, please join the Remind. If you could also email me at my school email address with the following: your preferred email address, your athlete’s name and the best phone number to reach you. This will help me get my list up and running.

I am looking forward to our upcoming season.

Coach Gregg Martin
gmartin@archie.k12.mo.us

Dear Parents and Guardians,
In order to best serve our students and school, the Re-Opening task force has prepared a survey to inform our decision-making process. We need parents to check their email and complete the survey by this Sunday evening (we will compile results before our next scheduled meeting which is Tuesday night). We appreciate your input as we prepare the best possible plan for reopening this coming school year.

If you have a Pre-K or Kindergarten student and would like to participate in the survey, please e-mail Tamara Stroud at tstroud@archie.k12.mo.us

text:
Dear Parents and Guardians,
In order to best serve our students and school, the Re-Opening task force has prepared a survey to inform our decision-making process. We need parents to check their email and complete the survey by this Sunday evening (we will compile results before our next scheduled meeting which is Tuesday night). We appreciate your input as we prepare the best possible plan for reopening this coming school year.

If you have a Pre-K or Kindergarten student and would like to participate in the survey, please e-mail Tamara Stroud at tstroud@archie.k12.mo.us

***Parents, please check your junk or spam mail if you did not receive the survey email.

post_text:
The Archie R-V School District has a $0.27 levy increase for operations purposes. The increase in revenue generated by the levy will be used to assist with the recruitment and retention of high quality educators.

This increase in levy places the District’s operating levy 5th out of 10 school districts in Cass County. The ballot question will read as follows:

Shall Archie R-V School District of Cass County, Missouri, be authorized to increase its operating tax levy by $0.27 per one hundred dollars of assessed valuation for operating expenses of the District, including increasing compensation for employees in order to attract and retain quality faculty and staff?

If this question is approved, the District’s operating tax levy is estimated to increase from the current operating levy of $3.7194 to $3.9894 per one hundred dollars of assessed valuation of real and personal property. We have included information regarding how the increase might impact your taxes here. Please Vote on Tuesday, June 2nd.

Wishing you good health! – Nurse Emma

2020 KC Scholars Announced: College Savings Match/College Savings Account (9th grade)
Each year, up to 500 9th graders will have a 529 college savings account seeded with $50 from KC Scholars. Of these 500 9th graders, at least 50 will be selected for the 4:1 match and incentives program and earn up to a one-time award of up to $7000.
Congratulations to Brunson Tenholder for receiving the College Savings Account award and to Rianna Heide for receiving the College Savings Match award. Thanks to KC Scholars, these students will get a head start on saving and planning for college.
For more information about the KC Scholars program, visit www.kcscholars.org.

post_text:
2020 KC Scholars Announced: Traditional (11th grade) Scholarship
From among over 1,700 applicants for the traditional scholarship, FOUR Archie High School juniors have been awarded a KC Scholars Traditional (11th grade) scholarship. Approximately 300 scholarships were awarded on May 1, to juniors attending high school in the following counties: Cass, Clay, Jackson, and Platte (in Missouri) and Johnson and Wyandotte (in Kansas).
Congratulations to Chesnie Baker, Andrew Diehl, Jacob Forgette and Dylan Sutton. These scholarship recipients have just been awarded a scholarship up to $50,000 for college. Each student will receive up to $10,000 per year, for up to five years, to one of the 17 KC Scholars colleges or universities.
For more information about the KC Scholars program, visit www.kcscholars.org.

Her highlights at Archie High School were memories made while playing sports such as volleyball, basketball, and softball. I am forever grateful.” Congratulations Mariah! We wish you well as you pursue your dental career!

UPDATE: Please e-mail Mrs. Johnson @ jstiles@archie.k12.mo.us If you are interested in cheering for the 2020-2021 season.

Do you have school spirit? Want to show your school spirit in a positive way? JOIN THE VARSITY CHEER SQUAD!!!! We are looking for students who will be in the 9-12 grades next cheer to join the cheer squad.

How: Contact Mrs. Johnson to let her know you are interested by May 3 so she can give you more details.

Why does she need to know by then-we need to get uniforms ordered for the fall, our uniforms are custom made and can take up to 8 weeks to be made, maybe longer. Also practice will begin in August and you will need 14 practices to be eligible to cheer at the first game.

Congratulations Makiah! We are excited to see you flourish in your future as you pursue your marketing and event planning career!

All winners were sent on to the Manningham Trust Student Poetry Contest and those results should be announced mid-May. Daniel’s poem will appear in the MSPS state anthology, The Grist.

1 Daniel Morris “Who You Truly Are” $25
2. Thomas Janssen “Lost in a Book” $15
3. Summer Roberts “Goodbye” $10
2nd Honorable Mention Emma King “This Trend Called Death”
5th Honorable Mention Briar McIntire “Outside”

post_text: Jacob Meinsen, a lifelong student at Archie, plans to become an EMT at a local fire station or hospital, while using his A+ to continue his education to complete a Paramedic associate’s degree. His long term goal is to become a flight medic with LifeFlight Eagle. Jake attended Cass Career Center for two years, completing their Fire Science and EMT programs. His passion, dedication and drive for those programs earned him a membership in the National Technical Honor Society. Looking back, Jake’s highlights of high school are earning his EMT certification and license as well as making the varsity baseball team 3 out of 4 years. Congratulations and good luck, Jake, as you pursue your goals in the medical field.

It is our goal to begin featuring seniors throughout the week on Facebook. Please watch our Facebook page for our featured seniors.

William Hartman, having attended Archie since kindergarten, has been accepted to the UMKC Six-Year Medical Program! This is quite an accomplishment, as this program is highly selective. William plans to pursue his medical degree so that he can become a Family Practice physician. Reflecting on high school, William recognizes winning the TSA state competition in Technology Problem Solving, along with Wyatt Fletcher, as a major accomplishment. That first place victory allowed them to attend the national TSA competition in Atlanta, GA. Being a three-sport athlete, he also recognizes attending state track as a highlight moment while in high school. Congratulations William! We are proud of your hard work and look forward to seeing your success as a doctor.

post_text:
Archie FFA Members Win Contest

Four members from the Archie FFA chapter competed in the National #Stayathome Quiz Bowl event, this past week. The event was sponsored and facilitated by www.judgingcard.com The competition was an online trivia contest about the FFA organization and general agricultural knowledge. The competition was open to all FFA members across the nation. The four members that competed from Archie were: Emma McIntire, Bayley Heider, Keara Mattingley and Elishia Payne. Archie placed first in Missouri out of 27 teams. Additionally, Emma McIntire was the highest scoring individual out of over 100 competitors in the state. Archie placed 11th in the nation out of over 500 teams. CONGRATULATIONS!!!

Tonight the Cass County Health Department confirmed a case of COVID-19 requiring hospitalization of an Archie resident. Due to this very recent information and our desire to take every precaution necessary, we are canceling tomorrow’s learning packet and resource pick up at the school. We will NOT have pick up tomorrow.

The administrative team will be meeting tomorrow to develop a new distribution plan. We will do all we can to ensure the safety of our students, staff and community. Further updates will be announced via the usual channels of communication as they are developed. The Archie R-V School District thanks you for your patience and cooperation during these uncertain times.

Archie Elementary students collected $1,087.49 during our Kids Kicking Cancer Campaign! All funds were given to Gannon’s Gang to help local families with children battling cancer. Mrs. Mell’s class collected the most money during the campaign. On Tuesday, they were able to “pie” their teacher or Ms. Silvey (mostly Ms. Silvey). A few students from the second and third place classes were chosen to “pie” Ms. Silvey as well. Last, but not least, some of the original Caring Whirlwinds, now seniors, got to join in on the fun. Thank you to Mrs. Botkin and the Caring Whirlwinds for leading this event!
We were able to snap some photos from the event.
